nateks.name: nateks

revisions.description: This MIB module defines variables and variable groups common to more than one type of equipment manufactured by Nateks Group.
Added sfpDDMmediaType sfpDDMpresence fields to SfpDDMEntry
Added Digital IO traps and compliance statements
Converted from SMIv1 version of NATEKS-MIB v1.2.

nateks.contactinfo: Vladimir Gudin Postal: 10A, Vesyolaya str. Moscow, 115516 Russian Federation Tel: +7 499 704 32 32 E-mail: gudin@nateks.ru

IntegerNumber.name: IntegerNumber
IntegerNumber.description: Number of some objects, for example, rows in the table. May be zero, if there are no objects or higher if there are some.

IntegerWithDecimal.name: IntegerWithDecimal
IntegerWithDecimal.description: Fixed-point value with one decimal digit. For example, 250 = 25, -105 = -10.5.

IntegerMillis.name: IntegerMillis
IntegerMillis.description: Fixed-point value with three decimal digits. For example, 25000 = 25, -10500 = -10.5.

systemReset.name: systemReset
systemReset.description: Writing reset(1) to maintReset perform a restart of the device. Read always returns readValue(2).

model.name: model
model.description: Model name, for example MGS-3C-RGN. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

id.name: id
id.description: Device ID, displayed in the main menu of the module. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

hardwareVersion.name: hardwareVersion
hardwareVersion.description: Version of the device's hardware. For examle: 1.0

softwareVersion.name: softwareVersion
softwareVersion.description: Version of the device's main software and, optionally, versions of firmware loaded in DSL chipsets, etc. (if present). For examle: 3.5.0.5.9/5.0

softwareDate.name: softwareDate
softwareDate.description: Build date of the device's main software in MM.DD.YYYY format. Empty string, if build date is not maintained by devices software.

subrackAddress.name: subrackAddress
subrackAddress.description: Address of the module in the FlexGain cassette. For modules that do not have such an address, a value of 0 is returned.

errorCode.name: errorCode
errorCode.description: Device-dependent error code. Normal value for errorCode is 0, i.e. device is fully operational. Any non-zero value indicates device hardware fault to management software.

configRW.name: configRW
configRW.description: Reading configRW results in reading the whole running config (as DUMP R in Megatrans 3C does). Writing configRW results in writing to startup config (as LOAD in Megatrans 3C does). This variable may be also used by devices, that do not maintain configValueTable and configGroupTable, to get/set their configuration.

configDefault.name: configDefault
configDefault.description: Writing integer value to configDefault applies default profile to the configuration. Values and contents of default profiles are device-dependent.

configNumberValues.name: configNumberValues
configNumberValues.description: Number of configuration values in device's configuration.

configValueTable.name: configValueTable
configValueTable.description: A list of configuration values. The number of entries is given by the value of configSize.

valueId.name: valueId
valueId.description: A unique index of configuration value. It is constant at least until main software of the module changes.

valueGroup.name: valueGroup
valueGroup.description: Index of values' configuration group in the configGroupTable.

valueName.name: valueName
valueName.description: A unique name of configuration value. It is constant at least until main software of the module changes. Usually, it remains constant through the lifecycle of the product.

valueStatus.name: valueStatus
valueStatus.description: Change status for a value. All values of valueType setNow(1) have unchanged(1) status. Status for values of valueType applyConfirm(2): Initially, all values have unchanged(1) status. When value is changed in new configuration, valueStatus is changed(2). When APPLY is made in respect of a value, valueStatus is applied(3). When CONFIRM is made for a value, valueStatus returns to unchanged(1). Status for values of type afterReset: If valueStartup is different from valueRunning, valueStatus is changed(2), otherwise unchanged(1).

valueStartup.name: valueStartup
valueStartup.description: Startup value of configuration variable. Write operation changes valueStartup for values of valueType afterReset(3), valueRunning for values of valueType setNow(1), valueNew for values of valueType applyConfirm(2).

valueRunning.name: valueRunning
valueRunning.description: Running value of configuration variable. Write operation changes valueStartup for values of valueType afterReset(3), valueRunning for values of valueType setNow(1), valueNew for values of valueType applyConfirm(2).

valueNew.name: valueNew
valueNew.description: New value of configuration variable. Write operation changes valueStartup for values of valueType afterReset(3), valueRunning for values of valueType setNow(1), valueNew for values of valueType applyConfirm(2).

configNumberGroups.name: configNumberGroups
configNumberGroups.description: Number of configuration groups in device's configuration.

configGroupTable.name: configGroupTable
configGroupTable.description: A list of configuration values. The number of entries is given by the value of configSize.

groupId.name: groupId
groupId.description: A unique index of configuration group. It is constant at least until main software of the module changes.

groupName.name: groupName
groupName.description: Name of configuration group. It is constant at least until main software of the module changes. Usually, it remains constant through the lifecycle of the product.

groupStatus.name: groupStatus
groupStatus.description: Change status for a groupvalue. All groups of groupType setNow(1) have unchanged(1) status. Status for groups of groupType applyConfirm(2): Initially, all values have unchanged(1) status. When some of group values are changed in new configuration, groupStatus is changed(2). When APPLY is made for a group, groupStatus is applied(3). When CONFIRM is made for a group, groupStatus returns to unchanged(1). Status for groups of type afterReset: If startup values in the group are different from running values, groupStatus is changed(2), otherwise unchanged(1). Writing applied(3) to the groupStatus makes APPLY operation on a group. APPLY operation is allowed only for groups of groupType applyConfirm(2). Other write operations should report error.

configApplyAll.name: configApplyAll
configApplyAll.description: Writing applyAll(1) to configApplyAll makes APPLY ALL operation. Read always returns readValue(2).

configConfirm.name: configConfirm
configConfirm.description: Writing confirm(1) to configConfirm makes CONFIRM operation. Read always returns readValue(2).

configBackup.name: configBackup
configBackup.description: Writing backup(1) to configBackup performs BACKUP operation. Read always returns readValue(2).

configRestore.name: configRestore
configRestore.description: Writing restore(1) to configRestore performs RESTORE operation. Read always returns readValue(2).

g826Table.name: g826Table
g826Table.description: A list of g826 statistics. Each consists of an interface index in interfaces table, statistics name and g826 statistics valuess.

g826Id.name: g826Id
g826Id.description: A unique index of this g826 statistics. It is constant at least between device reboots.

g826IfIndex.name: g826IfIndex
g826IfIndex.description: Index of interface in interfaces table, this g826 statistics is for.

g826Name.name: g826Name
g826Name.description: Name of the statistic, for example: E1-1-CRC4, E1-2-E-Bit.

g826StatReset.name: g826StatReset
g826StatReset.description: Writing reset(1) to g826StatReset restarts this g826 statistic. Read always returns readValue(2).

g826Reset.name: g826Reset
g826Reset.description: Writing reset(1) to g826Reset restarts all g826 statistics. Read always returns readValue(2).

ifG826Table.name: ifG826Table
ifG826Table.description: A list of g826 statistics. Each consists of an interface index in interfaces table, statistics name and g826 statistics valuess.

ifG826Id.name: ifG826Id
ifG826Id.description: A unique index of this g826 statistics. It is constant at least between device reboots.

ifG826IfIndex.name: ifG826IfIndex
ifG826IfIndex.description: Index of interface in interfaces table, this g826 statistics is for.

ifG826Name.name: ifG826Name
ifG826Name.description: Name of the statistic, for example: E1-1-CRC4, E1-2-E-Bit.

ifG826StatReset.name: ifG826StatReset
ifG826StatReset.description: Writing reset(1) to ifG826StatReset restarts this g826 statistic. Read always returns readValue(2).

alarmTable.name: alarmTable
alarmTable.description: A list of alarms. Each consists of an interface index in interfaces table, alarm name, value and cutoff information.

alarmId.name: alarmId
alarmId.description: A unique index of alarm. It is constant at least between device reboots.

alarmIfIndex.name: alarmIfIndex
alarmIfIndex.description: Index of interface in interfaces table, which state this alarm indicates. Alarms, that do not have associated interfaces (for example, maintenance alarms), should have index of management interface as alarmIfIndex.

alarmName.name: alarmName
alarmName.description: Name of the alarm, for example: LOS-S, BER-H.

alarmType.name: alarmType
alarmType.description: Alarm type. If none of alarm types is applicable to this alarm, all bits are zero.

alarmDisplayType.name: alarmDisplayType
alarmDisplayType.description: Simplified alarm type to be used in trap filters

alarmTrapEnable.name: alarmTrapEnable
alarmTrapEnable.description: Alarm trap generation setup: changes in alarm state will cause trap generation when the alarmTrapEnable is true.

ifAlarmTable.name: ifAlarmTable
ifAlarmTable.description: A two-dimentional array of alarms. Alarms are grouped by interface number.

ifAlarmId.name: ifAlarmId
ifAlarmId.description: A unique index of alarm within interface. It is constant at least between device reboots.

ifAlarmIfIndex.name: ifAlarmIfIndex
ifAlarmIfIndex.description: Index of interface in interfaces table, which state this alarm indicates. Alarms, that do not have associated interfaces (for example, maintenance alarms), should have index of management interface as alarmIfIndex.

ifAlarmName.name: ifAlarmName
ifAlarmName.description: Name of the alarm, for example: LOS-S, BER-H.

ifAlarmType.name: ifAlarmType
ifAlarmType.description: Alarm type. If none of alarm types is applicable to this alarm, all bits are zero.

ifAlarmDisplayType.name: ifAlarmDisplayType
ifAlarmDisplayType.description: Simplified alarm type to be used in trap filters

tlmTable.name: tlmTable
tlmTable.description: A list of tlms. Each consists of tlm name, setup and status information, and trap generation setup.

tlmId.name: tlmId
tlmId.description: A unique index of TLM. It is constant at least between device reboots.

tlmStatus.name: tlmStatus
tlmStatus.description: The status of the TLM: on, off or detected.

tlmLastStatusChange.name: tlmLastStatusChange
tlmLastStatusChange.description: The time of last TLM status change, counted from system start.

tlmSetup.name: tlmSetup
tlmSetup.description: TLM setup: normally open or normally closed. Writing to this variable will configure this TLM, if the device does support the write access to this variable.

tlmTrapEnable.name: tlmTrapEnable
tlmTrapEnable.description: TLM trap generation setup: changes in TLM status will cause trap generation when the tlmTrapEnable is true.

tlmClear.name: tlmClear
tlmClear.description: Writing reset(1) to tlmClear will clear the TLM history, and det state of all TLM indicators will become off state. Read always returns readValue(2).

dslUnitType.name: dslUnitType
dslUnitType.description: The type of the unit: line termination units (LTU) and network termination units (NTU) will have the modem(1) value. All types of regenerators have regenerator(2) value.

dslChannelTable.name: dslChannelTable
dslChannelTable.description: A list of DSL channels present on this device. Each consists of DSL index, ifIndex, setup and status information.

dslChannelId.name: dslChannelId
dslChannelId.description: A unique index of the DSL channel. It is constant for a given model.

dslChannelIfIndex.name: dslChannelIfIndex
dslChannelIfIndex.description: Index in interfaces table of this DSL channel.

dslChannelMode.name: dslChannelMode
dslChannelMode.description: The activation mode of this channel: either it is Master (xU-C) or Slave (xU-R).

dslChannelStandard.name: dslChannelStandard
dslChannelStandard.description: The G.Shdsl mode this channel is working in.

dslChannelClockReference.name: dslChannelClockReference
dslChannelClockReference.description: The G.Shdsl clock mode this channel is working in.

dslChannelLineCodeConfig.name: dslChannelLineCodeConfig
dslChannelLineCodeConfig.description: The configured line code of this channel.

dslChannelPSDConfig.name: dslChannelPSDConfig
dslChannelPSDConfig.description: The configured PSD mask (annex) of this channel.

dslChannelBaserateConfig.name: dslChannelBaserateConfig
dslChannelBaserateConfig.description: The configured base data rate (in 64kbit/s units) of this channel. 0 means auto.

dslChannelStatus.name: dslChannelStatus
dslChannelStatus.description: The activation status of this DSL channel.

dslChannelLineCode.name: dslChannelLineCode
dslChannelLineCode.description: Current working line code of this channel. If the link is down, this item has notAvailable(0) value.

dslChannelPSD.name: dslChannelPSD
dslChannelPSD.description: Current working PSD mask (annex) of this channel. If the link is down, this item has notAvailable(0) value.

dslChannelBaserate.name: dslChannelBaserate
dslChannelBaserate.description: Current working base data rate (in 64kbit/s units) of this channel. If the link is down, this item has 0 value.

dslChannelLineRate.name: dslChannelLineRate
dslChannelLineRate.description: Current working line rate in kbit/s of this channel. If the link is down, this item has 0 value.

dslChannelPayloadRate.name: dslChannelPayloadRate
dslChannelPayloadRate.description: Current working payload rate in kbit/s of this channel. If the link is down, this item has 0 value.

dslChannelNMR.name: dslChannelNMR
dslChannelNMR.description: Current noise margin rate for the DSL channel in dB.

dslChannelPowerBackoff.name: dslChannelPowerBackoff
dslChannelPowerBackoff.description: Current power backoff of the local side of the DSL channel in dB.

dslChannelFarEndPowerBackoff.name: dslChannelFarEndPowerBackoff
dslChannelFarEndPowerBackoff.description: Current far end power backoff of the DSL channel in dB.

dslChannelLoopAttenuation.name: dslChannelLoopAttenuation
dslChannelLoopAttenuation.description: Current loop attenuation of the DSL channel in dB.

dslChannelEOCNumber.name: dslChannelEOCNumber
dslChannelEOCNumber.description: The EOC number of the unit in this DSL link. xtuC 1 xtuR 2 repeater N=1..max N+2

dslChannelRegeneratorNumber.name: dslChannelRegeneratorNumber
dslChannelRegeneratorNumber.description: The number of regenerators in the link. This unit is not present on regenerators.

dslChannelRemotePower.name: dslChannelRemotePower
dslChannelRemotePower.description: The remote power status of the channel. This item is not present on regenerators. On devices without remote powering capability it is present and always shows off(2). on(1) means the remote power is turned on in configuration and remote power in turned on. off(2) means the remote power is turned off in configuration or remote power capability is not present in the device. alarm(3) means remote power is turned off for a certain amount of time because overcurrent protection has triggered or AC/DC leakage threshold was met.

dslChannelRemotePowerVoltage.name: dslChannelRemotePowerVoltage
dslChannelRemotePowerVoltage.description: Remote power voltage configuration for the channel. This item is not present on regenerators. On devices without remote powering capability it is present and always shows 0. If remote power is turned off for this channel in configuration, 0 is read from this item. If remote power is turned on for this channel in configuration, remote power nominal voltage is read from this item regardless of error status (it may be off due to overcurrent etc). This item appeared in MIB v0.9 and some devices may not support it.

dslGroupTable.name: dslGroupTable
dslGroupTable.description: This table contains information on multipair and 4-wire goups of DSL channels.

dslGroupId.name: dslGroupId
dslGroupId.description: A unique index of the DSL channel group. It is constant between changes of unit configuration.

dslGroupType.name: dslGroupType
dslGroupType.description: The type of channel grouping. type4wire(1) represent 4-wire method of channel aggregation. type2pair(2)-type4pair(4) represent the M-pair method of channel aggregation.

dslGroupMainChannel.name: dslGroupMainChannel
dslGroupMainChannel.description: This is the dslChannelId of the main channel in the multipair or 4-wire group. The configuration for all channels in the group is taken from the main channel. Only the main channel is mentioned in regenerator pairs when regenerator is working in multipair mode.

dslGroupChannel1.name: dslGroupChannel1
dslGroupChannel1.description: The first channel in the sequence of dslChannelId's of the channels in the multipair or 4-wire group. The main channel is mentioned amongst others.

dslGroupChannel2.name: dslGroupChannel2
dslGroupChannel2.description: The second channel in the sequence of dslChannelId's of the channels in the multipair or 4-wire group. The main channel is mentioned amongst others.

dslGroupChannel3.name: dslGroupChannel3
dslGroupChannel3.description: The third channel in the sequence of dslChannelId's of the channels in the multipair or 4-wire group. The main channel is mentioned amongst others. Only present for 3-pair and 4-pair groups.

dslGroupChannel4.name: dslGroupChannel4
dslGroupChannel4.description: The fourth channel in the sequence of dslChannelId's of the channels in the multipair or 4-wire group. The main channel is mentioned amongst others. Only present for 4-pair groups.

dslRegenerationChannels.name: dslRegenerationChannels
dslRegenerationChannels.description: The number of regenerator channels working in this device.

dslRegenerationTable.name: dslRegenerationTable
dslRegenerationTable.description: This table is a list of regenerator channels working in this device. Devices that do not have regenerator functions do not need to implement this table.

dslRegenerationId.name: dslRegenerationId
dslRegenerationId.description: A unique index of the DSL regeneration channel. It is constant between configuration changes.

dslRegenerationSide1.name: dslRegenerationSide1
dslRegenerationSide1.description: This is the dslChannelId of side 1 of the regeneration channel.

dslRegenerationSide2.name: dslRegenerationSide2
dslRegenerationSide2.description: This is the dslChannelId of side 2 of the regeneration channel.

indicationLedNumber.name: indicationLedNumber
indicationLedNumber.description: Number of LED indicators the device has.

indicationLedTable.name: indicationLedTable
indicationLedTable.description: A list LED indicators. Each consists of an LED index, textual description, populated/not populated status, current color and blinking rate.

indicationLedId.name: indicationLedId
indicationLedId.description: A unique index of the LED indicator. It is constant between different models of one device family.

indicationLedDescription.name: indicationLedDescription
indicationLedDescription.description: Description of LED indicator. May include name on the front/back panel of the device and/or place of the LED.

indicationLedState.name: indicationLedState
indicationLedState.description: The state of a LED. If the LED is not present, it's state is not-populated. If it is not lit, it's state is OFF. If it is lit, then a color is reported.

indicationLedFlash.name: indicationLedFlash
indicationLedFlash.description: If the LED is switching on and off at a constant rate, shows how is it blinking. Values from 1 to 14 represent a bit mask, where each bit shows, if the LED is lit during corresponding quarter of second: bit 0 - first quarter, bit 1 - second etc. If the LED is lit constantly, returns 'constant(15)'.

temperatureSensorNumber.name: temperatureSensorNumber
temperatureSensorNumber.description: Number of the temperature sensors the device has.

temperatureSensorTable.name: temperatureSensorTable
temperatureSensorTable.description: A list temperature sensors. First sensor in the list should always be the sensor that can be considered as 'Board temperature' sensor. For each sensor there is an identifier, description and the temperature value in 1/1000 of the Celcium degree.

temperatureSensorId.name: temperatureSensorId
temperatureSensorId.description: A unique index of the temperature sensor. It is constant between different models of one device family.

temperatureSensorDescription.name: temperatureSensorDescription
temperatureSensorDescription.description: Description of the temperature sensor. Should describe, where temperature is measured.

temperatureSensorValue.name: temperatureSensorValue
temperatureSensorValue.description: The temperature value in 1/1000 of the Celcium degree. For example, 25000 = 25C, -10500 = -10.5C.

timeSourceNumber.name: timeSourceNumber
timeSourceNumber.description: Number of device's UTC time sources.

timeSourceTable.name: timeSourceTable
timeSourceTable.description: Table of UTC time sources present on device. Examples are UTC, satellite (GNSS) etc.

timeSourceId.name: timeSourceId
timeSourceId.description: A unique index of the time source. It is constant between reconfigurations of a device.

timeSourceName.name: timeSourceName
timeSourceName.description: Name of the time source. For example: NTP.

timeSourceStratum.name: timeSourceStratum
timeSourceStratum.description: Clock source stratum as it is defined in NTP.

timeSourceValue.name: timeSourceValue
timeSourceValue.description: UTC time as reported by this source. If source is not ready (no connection to server or no signal), zero-length octet string is returned.

timeZone.name: timeZone
timeZone.description: Displacement, in minutes, of local time relative to UTC. For example, 240 is UTC+04:00 (Moscow Time), -480 is UTC-08:00 (Pacific Standard Time).

powerSourceNumber.name: powerSourceNumber
powerSourceNumber.description: Number of device's local power sources.

powerSourceTable.name: powerSourceTable
powerSourceTable.description: Table of local power sources available to the device, listed in priority order.

powerSourceId.name: powerSourceId
powerSourceId.description: A unique index of the power source.

powerSourceName.name: powerSourceName
powerSourceName.description: Name of the power source. For example: 48V-a.

powerSourceNominalVoltage.name: powerSourceNominalVoltage
powerSourceNominalVoltage.description: Nominal voltage of the power source.

powerSourceStatus.name: powerSourceStatus
powerSourceStatus.description: Availability status of this power source.

SfpPowerMilliWatt.name: SfpPowerMilliWatt
SfpPowerMilliWatt.description: SFP optical power from 0 to 6.5535 mW, in 1E-4 mW units.

sfpDDMNumber.name: sfpDDMNumber
sfpDDMNumber.description: Number of the sfp modules the device has.

sfpDDMTable.name: sfpDDMTable
sfpDDMTable.description: Table of DDM values read from SFP

sfpDDMTemperature.name: sfpDDMTemperature
sfpDDMTemperature.description: Internally measured transceiver temperature in range from -128C to +128C.

sfpDDMSupplyVoltage.name: sfpDDMSupplyVoltage
sfpDDMSupplyVoltage.description: Internally measured transceiver supply voltage in range from 0 to +6.5535 Volts.

sfpDDMTxBiasCurrent.name: sfpDDMTxBiasCurrent
sfpDDMTxBiasCurrent.description: Measured TX bias current in range from 0 to 131.0 mA

sfpDDMTxOutputmW.name: sfpDDMTxOutputmW
sfpDDMTxOutputmW.description: Measured TX output power in range from 0 to 6.5535 mW

sfpDDMTxOutputdBm.name: sfpDDMTxOutputdBm
sfpDDMTxOutputdBm.description: Measured TX output power in range from -40 to +8.2 dBm

sfpDDMRxInputmW.name: sfpDDMRxInputmW
sfpDDMRxInputmW.description: Measured RX received optical power from 0 to 6.5535 mW.

sfpDDMRxInputdBm.name: sfpDDMRxInputdBm
sfpDDMRxInputdBm.description: Measured RX received optical power from -40 to +8.2 dBm.

sfpDDMMediaType.name: sfpDDMMediaType
sfpDDMMediaType.description: This object returns sfpMedia type. when module is not mounted return value is unknown (3)

sfpDDMPresence.name: sfpDDMPresence
sfpDDMPresence.description: This object indicates if specified SFP interface plugged or not present (1) indicates that SFP interface is plugged. absent (2) indicates that SFP interface is unplugged.

sfpDDMIfIndex.name: sfpDDMIfIndex
sfpDDMIfIndex.description: Index of interface in interfaces table, which state this SFP interface represents.

ioDInNumber.name: ioDInNumber
ioDInNumber.description: Number of digital inputs the device has

ioDInTable.name: ioDInTable
ioDInTable.description: Discrete input table represents all discrete (digital) inputs present and configured in the device, including voltage inputs, dry contact inputs and any other.

dInId.name: dInId
dInId.description: A unique index of discrete input. It should remain constant through any reconfiguration and reboot of the device.

dInName.name: dInName
dInName.description: Discrete input name, typically - connector marking.

dInState.name: dInState
dInState.description: Discrete input state. For voltage input values are high(3) or low(4). For npn or dry contact input it is open(1) or closed(2).

dInNormalState.name: dInNormalState
dInNormalState.description: Normal discrete input state. If it is any(5), then input is considered informative, else it is has normal (normally open or normally closed) and alarm state.

dInAlarmSeverity.name: dInAlarmSeverity
dInAlarmSeverity.description: dInAlarmSeverity allows systemAlarm variable to be triggered by the state of the input. Setting its to no(1) means that systemAlarm is not triggered; setting its to nonurgent(2) or urgent(3) will trigger the systemAlarm if dInState is not equal to dInNormalState.

dInDescription.name: dInDescription
dInDescription.description: User configurable description: input purpose, meaning, net.

dInTrapEnable.name: dInTrapEnable
dInTrapEnable.description: If true(1), trap will be sent on each change of dInState. If false(2), no traps will be sent

ioDOutNumber.name: ioDOutNumber
ioDOutNumber.description: Number of digital outputs the device has

ioDOutTable.name: ioDOutTable
ioDOutTable.description: Discrete output table represents all discrete outputs present and configured in the device, including relay outputs, voltage outputs, and any other.

dOutId.name: dOutId
dOutId.description: A unique index of discrete output. It should remain constant through any reconfiguration and reboot of the device.

dOutName.name: dOutName
dOutName.description: Discrete output name, typically - connector marking.

dOutState.name: dOutState
dOutState.description: Discrete output state. For voltage output values are high(3) or low(4). For open-drain, npn, relay coil output (and other) it is active(1) or inactive(2). active(1) : coil energized, open-drain or npn output conducting current. inactive(2): coil de-energized, open-drain or npn output not conducting.

dOutNormalState.name: dOutNormalState
dOutNormalState.description: Normal discrete output state. If it is any(5), then input is considered informative, else it is has normal (normally open or normally closed) and alarm state.

dOutAlarmSeverity.name: dOutAlarmSeverity
dOutAlarmSeverity.description: dOutAlarmSeverity allows systemAlarm variable to trigger the state of the output. Setting its to no(1) means that systemAlarm will not trigger; setting its to nonurgent(2) or urgent(3) will trigger the output by changing the dOutState to the opposite of dOutNormalState.

dOutDescription.name: dOutDescription
dOutDescription.description: User configurable description: output purpose, connected load, net.

dOutTrapEnable.name: dOutTrapEnable
dOutTrapEnable.description: If true(1), trap will be sent on each change of dOutState. If false(2), no traps will be sent

statReset.name: statReset
statReset.description: Writing reset(1) perform a device statistics reset. All device statistics should be re-initialized. Read always returns readValue(2).

tftpServerIP.name: tftpServerIP
tftpServerIP.description: The IP address of the server from which the file is loaded. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each TFTP operation.

tftpSoftFileName.name: tftpSoftFileName
tftpSoftFileName.description: The remote filename for firmware upgrade. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each TFTP operation.

tftpConfFileName.name: tftpConfFileName
tftpConfFileName.description: The remote filename for the up and download the startup-config. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each TFTP operation.

tftpConnectionTimeout.name: tftpConnectionTimeout
tftpConnectionTimeout.description: Time the device will wait for reply from TFTP server, during connection and while transferring a block of data. While waiting, the device will retransmit it's request each 8 seconds (typically). Thus it is reasonable to set the timeout to a multiple of 8 seconds. If during tftpConnectionTimeout device will not get a responce from the server, current TFTP operation will be retried several times (set by tftpNumRetries) before ending with and error.

tftpNumRetries.name: tftpNumRetries
tftpNumRetries.description: Number of times the device will retry to connect and perform requested operation (firmware download, configuration up/download) before stopping with error status.

tftpTransCmd.name: tftpTransCmd
tftpTransCmd.description: This object, when read, always returns readValue(2). Setting this object will initiate following actions: swDownload(3) Download the firmware from TFTP server, filename on the server is specified by tftpSoftFileName. configDownload(4) Download the startup-config from the TFTP server, filename on the server is specified by tftpConfFileName. configUpLoad(5) Download the startup-config to the TFTP-Server, filename on the server is specified by tftpConfFileName. allDownload(6) Download the startup-config and firmware from the TFTP server. sdSwUpload(9) Upload software from main flash to SD card sdSwDownload(10) Download software from SD card sdConfigUpload(11) Upload the startup-config from main flash to SD card sdConfigDownload(12) Download the startup-config from SD card sdLoaderUpload(13) Upload bootloader from main flash to SD card sdLoaderDownload(14) Download bootloader from SD card sdCreateSnapshot(15) Upload Software, Loader and startup-config to SD card. Create filesystem if necesary noOp(1) Cancel all running SNMP-initiated TFTP operations. TFTP server IP address is configured by tftpServerIP variable. If device does not perform any other maintenance operations, the command will be executed, otherwise it will be denied. In case of command execution: The value of tftpLastOp will change to the value of the command. tftpTransferStatus will reflect transfer progress (connecting- transferringData-endedOk/error). Current timestamp will be saved into tftpLastOpTime variable. During the execution a series of tftpStatusChange is sent. In case of denial: tftpLastOp and tftpTransferStatus will not be affected. Current timestamp is also not saved into tftpLastOpTime variable. By quering tftpLastOpTime before and after setting the tftpTransCmd one can find out if the command was denied. Current operation that caused the denial can be queried by tftpLastOp. tftpStatusChange with tftpTransferStatus value of busyByOther is sent.

tftpLastOp.name: tftpLastOp
tftpLastOp.description: This object returns the last executed maintenance operation, regardless was it successful or not. It reports following actions: noOp(1) No maintenance operations were requested since last restart of the device. tftpSwDownload(3) Software download initiated from SNMP. tftpConfigDownload(4) Startup-config download initiated from SNMP. tftpConfigUpload(5) Startup-config upload initiated from SNMP. otherSwDownload(6) Software download, either TFTP or any other way, not initiated from SNMP. otherConfigDownload(7) Startup-config download, either TFTP or any other way, not initiated from SNMP. otherConfigUpload(8) Startup-config upload, either TFTP or any other way, not initiated from SNMP. sdSwUpload(9) Upload software from main flash to SD card sdSwDownload(10) Download software from SD card sdConfigUpload(11) Upload the startup-config from main flash to SD card sdConfigDownload(12) Download the startup-config from SD card sdLoaderUpload(13) Upload bootloader from main flash to SD card sdLoaderDownload(14) Download bootloader from SD card sdCreateSnapshot(15) Upload Software, Loader and startup-config to SD card. Create filesystem if necesary

tftpTransferStatus.name: tftpTransferStatus
tftpTransferStatus.description: Status of SNMP-initiated TFTP transfer. Results: noOp(1) Default, no TFTP operation was in progress. connecting(2) Device is connecting to the server specified by tftpServerIP. transferringData(3) TFTP data transfer is in progress. endedOk(4) TFTP transfer ended with success. error(5) TFTP data transfer ended with an Error, (e.g. server timeout or remote filename not found). Check TFTP server log file for details. busyByOther(6) This value can never be read directly from the MIB tree. It is used only in tftpStatusChange to notify that device is bysy with other maintenance operation and the request for another operation was denied. If tftpLastOp is tftpSwDownload(3), tftpConfigDownload(4) or tftpConfigUpload(5), this variable shows the status of exactly that operation. Transfers initiated by other means (for example CLI command TFTP operation or normal software download), do not change this variable. This way one can get full status of SNMP-initiated up/download without interference.

tftpLastOpTime.name: tftpLastOpTime
tftpLastOpTime.description: The time in timeticks when last maintenance operation (TFTP software download or configuration up/download) was executed from SNMP by setting tftpTransCmd. If operation execution was denied, this variable is not affected. By comparing tftpLastOpTime before and after tftpTransCmd setting one can find out if the command was successful or denied.

tftpSoftConfirm.name: tftpSoftConfirm
tftpSoftConfirm.description: Writing softConfirm(1) to tftpSoftConfirm will confirm previously uploaded firmware. Read always returns readValue(2).

tftpProtocolVersion.name: tftpProtocolVersion
tftpProtocolVersion.description: Allows protocol selection between tftp(1), ftp(2) and sftp(3) for up/download. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each operation.

tftpServerUserName.name: tftpServerUserName
tftpServerUserName.description: The Username for Server access. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each operation.

tftpServerUserPass.name: tftpServerUserPass
tftpServerUserPass.description: The User Password for Server access. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each operation.

tftpServerPortNumber.name: tftpServerPortNumber
tftpServerPortNumber.description: The port number for accessing FTP or SFTP server. This value is not stored between device reboots and should be set before each operation.

macFilterConfigTable.name: macFilterConfigTable
macFilterConfigTable.description: Table representing MAC-based filter configuration of network interfaces.

macFilterConfigEntry.name: macFilterConfigEntry
macFilterConfigEntry.description: MAC-based filter configuration of one interface

macFilterConfigIfIndex.name: macFilterConfigIfIndex
macFilterConfigIfIndex.description: Index in interfaces table of the configured interface.

macFilterConfigStatus.name: macFilterConfigStatus
macFilterConfigStatus.description: Indicates, whether filtering is on(1) or off(2).

macFilterConfigAction.name: macFilterConfigAction
macFilterConfigAction.description: Security action when non-permitted frame is received: filter - just drop the frame; indicate - drop the frame and send trap; block - drop the frame, send trap and permanently block the interface.

macFilterWhitelistTable.name: macFilterWhitelistTable
macFilterWhitelistTable.description: White list of allowed MAC addresses.

macFilterViolationsTable.name: macFilterViolationsTable
macFilterViolationsTable.description: List of several last MAC address security violations.

macFilterViolationsTimestamp.name: macFilterViolationsTimestamp
macFilterViolationsTimestamp.description: Timestamp of last time an action was taken against security violation performed by this MAC address on this interface. Measured in 1/100s of second from the last start of the unit - same as sysUpTime.

tlmStatusChange.name: tlmStatusChange
tlmStatusChange.description: A tlmStatusChange trap is sent when the value of an instance tlmStatus changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger polls.

alarmValueChange.name: alarmValueChange
alarmValueChange.description: A alarmValueChange trap is sent when alarm value changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger polls.

tftpStatusChange.name: tftpStatusChange
tftpStatusChange.description: This trap is sent during the process of SNMP-initiated TFTP maintenance command (TFTP software download or configuration up/download) to report current execution status. In this case tftpLastOp shows the current operation, tftpLastOpTime indicates starting time of current operation, tftpTransferStatus indicates status of the transfer. If the command is denied, this trap is also sent with tftpTransferStatus value of busyByOther. In this case tftpLastOp indicates the operation that conflicted with the command.

macFilterViolation.name: macFilterViolation
macFilterViolation.description: This trap is sent to indicate that MAC filter access violation has happened and specific security action will be performed. Variables: macFilterViolationsIfIndex, ifDescr - index and name of interface; macFilterViolationsMAC - violating MAC; macFilterConfigAction - action to be performed.

dInStateChange.name: dInStateChange
dInStateChange.description: This trap is sent to indicate that input state has changed.

dOutStateChange.name: dOutStateChange
dOutStateChange.description: This trap is sent to indicate that output state has changed.
